body:
Ok, I'd like to help, but I really don't feel like making a PR on a thing I don't fully understand.
Let's try it at least in comments - 

If I look at the commit https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/commit/aead65f2d22e8b675cf4a1f2f50ee8ba8ef7f2a1 by qiangxue, could we just edit the all() method in similar manner?
Instead of this

```php
if ($this->emulateExecution) {
    return [];
}
$rows = $this->createCommand($db)->queryAll();
return $this->populate($rows);
```

I made small changes to this: 

```php
if ($this->emulateExecution) {
    return [];
}

if (is_array($this->select) && !in_array($this->indexBy, $this->select)) {
    $this->select[] = $this->indexBy;
}

$rows = $this->createCommand($db)->queryAll();
return $this->populate($rows);
```

I changed the condition a bit to suit a better to the spirit of all(). It works as expected on my personal test, but I can't be sure it will work in many other real-life scenarios.
Maybe you with your in depth knowledge can see if this solutions has some obvious catch.
